http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/Rs.-4-lakh-penalty-levied-on-illegal-stone-quarrying/article13986324.ece

A team of officials of the Mines and Geology Department led by geologist Somashekhar conducted raids on illegal stone quarrying in different parts of Tekal hobli in Malur taluk on Wednesday. Notices were served and a sum of Rs. 4 lakh has been levied on the accused quarry owners as penalty, Mr. Somashekhar said.Raids were conducted in Halepalya, Janganahalli, Kadirenahalli, Ullerahalli, Huligutte, Hunasikote and other areas following complaints by the public about illegal quarrying, he said.